      {
        "id": "decf57cd6d508f1e53c96b83080e0e428f74a795",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 3239,
          "name": "Ram Krishna Verma",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "ramkrishna.verma@gmail.com",
          "username": "ramverma"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2021-05-27 16:35:02.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 5: Code-Review-1\n\nI don't think we need this change. As agreed earlier, we decided that PDP will always send the full list in the PDP_STATUS message to PAP. So, there is no need to compare delta deployment list.",
        "patchset_number": 5
      },
      {
        "id": "9f64a5aaee78b4aa992460200c261831fb65e516",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 811,
          "name": "Jim Hahn",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "jrh3@att.com",
          "username": "jrh3"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2021-05-27 16:59:05.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 5:\n\n> Patch Set 5: Code-Review-1\n> \n> I don't think we need this change. As agreed earlier, we decided that PDP will always send the full list in the PDP_STATUS message to PAP. So, there is no need to compare delta deployment list.\n\nWe still need these changes, because the existing PAP code still uses the full policy list from the PdpUpdate request when determining success/failure; that field is being deprecated, so PAP must be modified to use the new fields when comparing the response",
        "patchset_number": 5
      },
      {
        "id": "c2bf070f70fc72b1e3591875ea06d7b1fa712e02",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 4903,
          "name": "Ajith Sreekumar",
          "display_name": "Ajith Sreekumar",
          "email": "ajith.sreekumar@bell.ca",
          "username": "a.sreekumar"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2021-05-27 17:06:28.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 5:\n\n> Patch Set 5:\n> \n> > Patch Set 5: Code-Review-1\n> > \n> > I don't think we need this change. As agreed earlier, we decided that PDP will always send the full list in the PDP_STATUS message to PAP. So, there is no need to compare delta deployment list.\n> \n> We still need these changes, because the existing PAP code still uses the full policy list from the PdpUpdate request when determining success/failure; that field is being deprecated, so PAP must be modified to use the new fields when comparing the response\n\nNot sure I understand correctly. I thought PDPs are going to send back full list(received in policiesToBeDeployed + what was already deployed) in \"policies\" field in PDP_STATUS message. PAP should probably receive this, and check if all policies it sent in policiesToBeDeployed list are in the \"policies\" list in PDP_STATUS response.\nNext change we need is, to remove the usage of \"policies\" field from PDP_UPDATE message, and then remove the same from models.\nIs my understanding correct? or am I missing something here?",
        "patchset_number": 5
      },
      {
        "id": "6419a2afa03d4dce0647d5325b8f430175cdfd6f",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 811,
          "name": "Jim Hahn",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "jrh3@att.com",
          "username": "jrh3"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2021-05-27 17:14:27.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 5:\n\n> Not sure I understand correctly. I thought PDPs are going to send back full list(received in policiesToBeDeployed + what was already deployed) in \"policies\" field in PDP_STATUS message. PAP should probably receive this, and check if all policies it sent in policiesToBeDeployed list are in the \"policies\" list in PDP_STATUS response.\n> Next change we need is, to remove the usage of \"policies\" field from PDP_UPDATE message, and then remove the same from models.\n> Is my understanding correct? or am I missing something here?\n\nThat's my understanding, too.  So this change is needed to address your comment above, \"PAP should probably receive this, and check...\"",
        "patchset_number": 5
      },
