        "message": "Patch Set 5:\n\n> Patch Set 5:\n> \n> > Patch Set 5:\n> > \n> > > Patch Set 5: Code-Review-1\n> > > \n> > > I don't think we need this change. As agreed earlier, we decided that PDP will always send the full list in the PDP_STATUS message to PAP. So, there is no need to compare delta deployment list.\n> > \n> > We still need these changes, because the existing PAP code still uses the full policy list from the PdpUpdate request when determining success/failure; that field is being deprecated, so PAP must be modified to use the new fields when comparing the response\n> \n> Not sure I understand correctly. I thought PDPs are going to send back full list(received in policiesToBeDeployed + what was already deployed) in \"policies\" field in PDP_STATUS message. PAP should probably receive this, and check if all policies it sent in policiesToBeDeployed list are in the \"policies\" list in PDP_STATUS response.\n> Next change we need is, to remove the usage of \"policies\" field from PDP_UPDATE message, and then remove the same from models.\n> Is my understanding correct? or am I missing something here?\n\n@Ajith - I agree with your suggestion. May be the code needs to be reworked and commit title and message updated accordingly?",
